<br />
NOTE - the CDC seems to define a child as someone who is 14 years old or younger.<br />
<br />
NOTE - 2010 is the most recent year that the full data is available.<br />
<br />
In 2010 there were 211 kids killed in car accidents where alcohol was a factor in the crash.<br />
<br />
In 2010 there were 62 accidental (or &#39;unintentional&#39;) children deaths due to firearms.<br />
<br />
Both are incredibly tragic and awful, and we should be trying to prevent them, but to imply that the latter happens all the time probably reflects the way the news is reported.<br />
